The paper deals with cyberattack detection, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed method uses deep generative models with variational inference, which involves machine learning techniques such as artificial intelligence (cs.AI), deep learning (cs.LG), and neural networks (cs.NE). The study also focuses on infrastructure systems cybersecurity, which could be classified under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
